article.headline: Wichita St. 79, W. Carolina 63
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. -- Cleanthony Early scored 21 points as Wichita State beat Western Carolina 79-63 in the first round of the Cancun Challenge on Thursday night. Early was 6 of 11 from the field and had eight rebounds. Carl Hall scored 16 points and Evan Wessel added 11 for the Shockers (3-0). Wichita State led at halftime 46-27. Trey Sumler scored 18 points, including four 3-pointers, for the Catamounts (1-2). Tom Tankelewicz added 12 points. Brandon Boggs and Tawaski King scored 11 each. King led the team with seven rebounds.
